## 🚀 Key Highlights

- ACID-compliant money transfers
- Concurrency-safe balance updates
- Idempotent transfer API
- Append-only ledger system
- Soft delete & restore lifecycle
- Optimized database indexing
- Clean layered architecture
- Dockerized development setup
- Swagger (OpenAPI) documentation

---

## 🧩 Features

### 1️⃣ Wallet Management

- Create wallet
- List wallets
- Get wallet by ID
- Deposit funds
- Withdraw funds
- Soft delete wallet
- Restore wallet

---

### 2️⃣ Transfers

- Atomic wallet-to-wallet transfers
- Row-level locking (`SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`)
- Idempotency key enforcement

---

### 3️⃣ Ledger System

- DEPOSIT
- WITHDRAW
- TRANSFER_OUT
- TRANSFER_IN

---

## ⚡ Performance Optimization

- Index on `(from_wallet_id, idempotency_key)`
- Index on `wallet_id`
- Index on `created_at`

---

## 🏗 Architecture

```
src/
  routes/
  services/
  db/
  middleware/
  utils/
```

---

## 🧠 Core Engineering Concepts

### Atomic Transactions

```sql
BEGIN;
SELECT ... FOR UPDATE;
UPDATE wallets ...;
INSERT ledger_entries ...;
COMMIT;
```

### Row-Level Locking

```sql
SELECT ... FOR UPDATE;
```

### Idempotency

- Prevent duplicate transfers
- Safe retries
- Conflict detection

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- Node.js
- Express.js
- PostgreSQL
- Docker
- Jest & Supertest

---

## 📦 Requirements

- Node.js (v18+)
- Docker
- Git

---

## 🐳 Run with Docker (Recommended)

### 1. Create .env

```env
PORT=3000
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@db:5432/walletdb
```

### 2. Start

```bash
npm run docker:up
```

### 3. Migrate

```bash
npm run docker:migrate
```

---

## 💻 Run Without Docker (Optional)

```bash
npm install
createdb -U postgres walletdb
npm run migrate
npm run dev
```

